Gregory Brown is the author of <a href="http://rubybestpractices.com">Ruby Best Practices</a> and an all-around crunchy person. He took off half a year in 2008 to work on the PDF generation library "Prawn":http://prawn.majesticseacreature.com, supported by the "kindness of the Ruby community":http://majesticseacreature.com/mendicant. Gregory lives in New Haven, CT with his girlfriend, some small animals, and a bamboo plant that seems to live without water.

h3. Upcoming Events

* Speaking at "GoRuCo":http://goruco.com May 30th, 2009
* RBP generally available for purchase: June 15th, 2009

h3. Contact

Gregory can be found on Twitter as "@rubypractices":http://twitter.com/rubypractices and "@seacreature":http:/twitter.com/seacreature .

He also runs the "Majestic Sea Creature":http://majesticseacreature.com blog, and if you're really interested in stalking him, his non-technical writings are at "Meta-Metta":http://meta-metta.blogspot.com

